# Conventional Commits

Parfumbox uses **release-please** with unified semver. Every commit message must follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) (enforced by commitlint + husky).

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Types (use these)

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New user-facing behavior |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `refactor` | Code change without behavior change |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config |
| `ci` | CI/CD changes |

## Breaking changes

Use `feat!:` / `fix!:` or a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer for major version bumps.

## Examples

```
feat: add admin order export CSV
fix: validate Telegram initData expiry
chore: add release-please workflow
docs: document GET /version endpoint
```

## Do not

- Use vague messages (`update`, `fix bugs`, `wip`).
- Bump `version` in package.json manually — release-please handles releases.
- Edit `CHANGELOG.md` by hand.

See [docs/RELEASING.md](../../docs/RELEASING.md) for the full release flow.
